<%# Shared COMMAND/SEARCH terminal-style input bar (R6/R7, architecture plan file/module
    layout table). One physical bar/input, reused for both modes -- only the leading
    glyph (":" vs "/"), the sr-only label text, and the placeholder copy differ per mode,
    swapped by keyboard_nav_controller.js#enterBarMode() at mode entry (COMMAND_BAR_COPY);
    the input's own input/keydown Stimulus actions dispatch on the controller's current
    mode Value rather than duplicating this markup for a second bar. COMMAND mode
    (Increment 3) wired the `:` path; this increment (Increment 4, SEARCH) adds the `/`
    path plus the results list below the input.

    Plain-CSS `hidden` by default (nothing to flash without JS, matching the status
    line's own convention); enterBarMode()/exitToNormal() toggle visibility directly and
    synchronously at the entry/exit point (not via modeValueChanged() -- see that
    method's comment for why anything focus/visibility-ordering-sensitive can't wait on
    Stimulus's async Value-changed callback). The <input> is a real,
    <label class="sr-only">-labeled field (R11) -- never a focus trap. %>
<div
  id="keyboard-command-bar"
  data-keyboard-nav-target="commandBar"
  class="hidden fixed bottom-0 inset-x-0 z-40 font-mono text-sm bg-base-200 text-base-content border-t border-base-300"
>
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-3 py-2 flex items-center gap-2">
    <label for="keyboard-command-input" class="sr-only" data-keyboard-nav-target="commandLabel">Command</label>
    <span aria-hidden="true" class="text-primary" data-keyboard-nav-target="commandGlyph">:</span>
    <input
      type="text"
      id="keyboard-command-input"
      data-keyboard-nav-target="commandInput"
      data-action="input->keyboard-nav#handleBarInput keydown->keyboard-nav#handleBarKeydown"
      autocomplete="off"
      autocapitalize="off"
      spellcheck="false"
      class="flex-1 bg-transparent outline-none"
      placeholder="home | writing | projects | resume | theme &lt;name&gt; | help"
    />
  </div>
  <div
    data-keyboard-nav-target="commandFeedback"
    aria-live="polite"
    class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-3 pb-2 text-xs text-base-content/80 empty:hidden"
  ></div>
  <%# SEARCH mode's live-filtered results list (R7). Empty (and CSS-hidden via
      `empty:hidden`) in COMMAND mode and until SEARCH's index has loaded --
      keyboard_nav_controller.js#renderSearchResults populates each <li> with a real
      <a href> (never a hand-built href -- each item's `url` was already built
      server-side via post_url/project_url, R9), so Enter's .click() (commitSearch) is a
      genuine link activation, and a mouse/touch visitor can click a result directly. %>
  <ul
    id="keyboard-search-results"
    data-keyboard-nav-target="searchResults"
    aria-label="Search results"
    class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-3 pb-2 max-h-64 overflow-y-auto empty:hidden space-y-0.5"
  ></ul>
</div>
